         <abstract>
            <p>The operating cycle is the length of time from the receipt of raw materials until the collection of cash from the sale of finished goods and is equal to the days in inventory plus the days sales outstanding. Days in inventory can be decomposed into days raw material on hand, days in production, and days finished goods on hand. This enhanced version of the operating cycle allows fora more meaningful analysis of changes in a firm's inventory and accounts receivables policies. This enhancement is shown by analyzing changes in inventory management and production techniques at A. T. Cross Company.</p>
         </abstract>
